name: Rita Rossweisse (Fallen Rosemary) | Honkai Impact 3rd | LoRA
description:
A LoRA Model of Rita Rossweisse from Honkai Impact 3rd.

This LoRA includes two official costumes.

There are two sets of trigger words:

For trigger Fallen Rosemary:

rita rossweisse (fallen rosemary), rita rossweisse, dress, choker, brown hair, long hair, detached sleeves, hair over one eye, eyes visible through hair, hair flower, blue rose, red eyes, swept bangs, asymmetrical sleeves, mole under eye

For trigger Summer Night's Dream:

rita rossweisse (summer night's dream), rita rossweisse, shirt, pantyhose, red rose, brown hair, long hair, long sleeves, red eyes, mole under eye, hair over one eye, frilled shirt, white shirt

bonus: For trigger Any Custom Outfit:

rita rossweisse, brown hair, red eyes, mole under eye, hair over one eye, eyes visible through hair, short hair

Recommend 0.85-1 Strength for triggering any official costume.

For changing custom clothes, I suggest 0.7-0.85 Weight

The preview images were generated by AbyssOrangeMix2 Model.

In some instances applied ControlNet.

I am using the NAI model [e6e8e1fc] to train

Able to work with all mixed models based on NAI(i.e. AbyssOrangeMix, Anything v3)

If you like this LORA, please comment and give it a like.❤️

Any suggestions are welcome to comment here.

And also welcome to share your creations.

Enjoy it!

modelVersions.name: v1.1
modelVersions.description:
Happy Birthday Rita🎉🎉

Update:

Improve the resolution of data set.

No longer train with the VAE model during model training in order to work with Latent Couple and Composable LoRA.

Reduce "Noise Offset" parms.

Use Lion Optimizer instant of 8bit adam.

Known Issue:

This version has a little bit overfitting, some clothing elements will still stubbornly show up when you trigger any custom outfit.

Some image quality issue when work with Latent Couple and Composable LoRA. (Use Euler a Sampling method instead of DPM++ 2M Karras when you encounter quality issue)

Planned update:

  • Improve tagging

  • Add more official costumes

  • Adjust training parameters
